qosIfTable.name: qosIfTable
qosIfTable.description: The qosIfTable enables QoS policies on the interface specified by qosIfIndex (interface index). Creating entries: Entries are created by assigning a value to the qosIfIndex object. Deleting entries: Entries are removed by setting an entry's qosIfType object to 'delete'.

qosIfType.name: qosIfType
qosIfType.description: This object defines the queueing and scheduling algorithm used on the related interface, possible values: pq(1) = priority queueing wrr(2) = weighted round-robin scheduling wfq(3) = weighted fair queuing scheduling disable(8) = disable this entry delete(9) = delete this entry.

qosIfMaxTxRate.name: qosIfMaxTxRate
qosIfMaxTxRate.description: This object enables traffic shaping on the related interface, if set to zero (0) there is no shaping active. Otherwise this variable defines the maximum amount of bits per second to be transmitted.

qosIfStatTable.name: qosIfStatTable
qosIfStatTable.description: The qosIfStatTable contains statistical QoS-specific information for the interface specified by qosIfStatIndex (interface index). Only the system can add or delete entries to this table.

qosIfStatOutPkts.name: qosIfStatOutPkts
qosIfStatOutPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted on the related interface since its last change to the 'up' state.

qosIfStatOutOctets.name: qosIfStatOutOctets
qosIfStatOutOctets.description: The number of octets transmitted on the related interface since its last change to the 'up' state.

qosIfStatPktsQueued.name: qosIfStatPktsQueued
qosIfStatPktsQueued.description: The number of data packets enqueued and waiting to be sent across the related interface.

qosIfStatOctetsQueued.name: qosIfStatOctetsQueued
qosIfStatOctetsQueued.description: The amount of data (in octets) enqueued waiting to be sent across the related interface.

qosIfStatPktsDropped.name: qosIfStatPktsDropped
qosIfStatPktsDropped.description: The number of data packets dropped during congestion.

qosIfStatOctetsDropped.name: qosIfStatOctetsDropped
qosIfStatOctetsDropped.description: The representation of qosIfStatPktsDropped in octets.

qosPolicyTable.name: qosPolicyTable
qosPolicyTable.description: The qosPolicyTable enables QoS policies for the packet class specified by qosPolicyIfIndex (interface index), qosPolicyType and qosPolicyClassId. Creating entries: Entries are created by assigning a value to the qosPolicyIfIndex object. Deleting entries: Entries are removed by setting an entry's qosPolicyType object to 'delete'.

qosPolicyType.name: qosPolicyType
qosPolicyType.description: This objects defines in conjunction with ipQoSClassId and qosPolicyClassId the related type of packet classes for this QoS policy, possible values: class-based(1) = policy for non-high-priority packets high-priority(2) = policy for high-priority packets default(3) = policy for packets not matching otherwise.

qosPolicyClassId.name: qosPolicyClassId
qosPolicyClassId.description: Defines in conjunction with ipQoSClassId and qosPolicyType the QoS policy to be applied on the classified IP traffic.

qosPolicyPriority.name: qosPolicyPriority
qosPolicyPriority.description: The relative priority for this packet class to be used for the packet scheduling as described via qosIfType.

qosPolicyWeight.name: qosPolicyWeight
qosPolicyWeight.description: The relative weight for this packet class to be used for the packet scheduling as described via qosIfType.

qosPolicyShaper.name: qosPolicyShaper
qosPolicyShaper.description: This objects describes the traffic-shaping algorithm to be used in order to limit the bandwidth for the related packet class, possible values: none(1) = no shaping defined token-bucket(2) = token-bucket traffic shaper.

qosPolicyCongestionAvoidance.name: qosPolicyCongestionAvoidance
qosPolicyCongestionAvoidance.description: This objects defines a packet dropping algorithm to use if more than qosPolicyLowerThreshold octets are enqueued.

qosPolicyDropAlgorithm.name: qosPolicyDropAlgorithm
qosPolicyDropAlgorithm.description: This objects defines the packet dropping algorithm to apply if more than qosPolicyUpperThreshold octets are currently enqueued, possible values: tail-drop(1) = drop all newly arriving packets head-drop(2) = drop packets at the queue head enqueue newly arriving packets random-drop(3) = drop arriving or enqueued packets randomly.

qosPolicyTxRate.name: qosPolicyTxRate
qosPolicyTxRate.description: This object enables bandwidth limitation for the related class, if set to zero (0) there is no limitation policy. Otherwise this variable defines the maximum amount of bits per second to be send.

qosPolicyTxRateLimitation.name: qosPolicyTxRateLimitation
qosPolicyTxRateLimitation.description: This objects determines the policy for the related class if the transmission rate limit defined by qosPolicyTxRate is reached. When set to not-bounded(1) allocation of remaining bandwidth not consumed by other classes is allowed. When set to bounded(2), qosPolicyTxRate is strict limitation for the long-term bandwidth consumption.

qosPolicyTxBurstSize.name: qosPolicyTxBurstSize
qosPolicyTxBurstSize.description: The maximum number of octets in a single transmission burst.

qosPolicyLowerThreshold.name: qosPolicyLowerThreshold
qosPolicyLowerThreshold.description: This variable defines the lower or minimum queue depth threshold for packet dropping algorithm used for congestion avoidance (see qosPolicyCongestionAvoidance).

qosPolicyUpperThreshold.name: qosPolicyUpperThreshold
qosPolicyUpperThreshold.description: This variable defines the upper or maximum queue depth threshold at which - depending on qosPolicyDropAlgorithm - all newly arriving or packets enqueued former will be dropped.

qosPolicyStatTable.name: qosPolicyStatTable
qosPolicyStatTable.description: The qosPolicyStatTable contains statistical QoS-specific information for the policy specified by qosPolicyStatIfIndex (interface index), qosPolicyStatType and qosPolicyStatClassId. Only the system can add or delete entries to this table.

qosPolicyStatType.name: qosPolicyStatType
qosPolicyStatType.description: The related type of packet classes for this QoS policy (see qosPolicyType for further explanation).

qosPolicyStatOutPkts.name: qosPolicyStatOutPkts
qosPolicyStatOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent belonging to the related packet class.

qosPolicyStatOutOctets.name: qosPolicyStatOutOctets
qosPolicyStatOutOctets.description: The representation of qosPolicyStatOutPkts in octets.

qosPolicyStatPktsQueued.name: qosPolicyStatPktsQueued
qosPolicyStatPktsQueued.description: The number of data packets of the related class enqueued and waiting to be sent.

qosPolicyStatOctetsQueued.name: qosPolicyStatOctetsQueued
qosPolicyStatOctetsQueued.description: The representation of qosPolicyStatPktsQueued in octets.

qosPolicyStatPktsDropped.name: qosPolicyStatPktsDropped
qosPolicyStatPktsDropped.description: The number of data packets of the related class dropped during congestion.

qosPolicyStatOctetsDropped.name: qosPolicyStatOctetsDropped
qosPolicyStatOctetsDropped.description: The representation of qosPolicyStatPktsDropped in octets
